In a 6 qt braising pan or Dutch oven render the bacon on MEDIUM-HIGH heat until crisp. Remove the bacon. Add the potatoes and cook for 2 minutes while stirring. Add the pepper stir-fry mix and garlic and cook for 3 minutes more. Add the white wine, corn and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes more. Season with salt and pepper. Add the clams and cover. Continue to cook the mixture, stirring occasionally until the clams open, about 7 to 10 minutes. Remove clams to 4 pasta bowls to serve. Stir the cream, bacon and parsley into the broth and vegetable mixture and serve over the clams.